ue},"birth":{"year":1681,"month":9,"day":21,"city":"Hatfield","county":"Hampshire County","state":"Massachusetts","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1756,"month":2,"day":1,"city":"Durham","county":"Middlesex County","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"parents":{"father_id":"X01902","mother_research_notes":"Abigail Strong"},"marriages":[],"number_of_marriages":1,"tags":["minister","yale_alumni","yale_fellow","old_light"],"sources":[{"short":"Yale Biographical Sketches","url":"https://archive.org/details/cu31924092714488/page/12/mode/2up?q=chauncey"}],"notable":{"is_notable":true,"notable_category":["religion","academia"],"notable_blurb":"Yale 1702 first M.A.; Durham minister 50 years","primary_url":"https://archive.org/details/cu31924092714488/page/12/mode/2up?q=chauncey","primary_url_label":"Yale Biographical Sketches"},"narrative_blocks":[{"header":"Yale's first M.A. recipient","detail":"The son of a Harvard graduate and great-grandson of Harvard's second president, Nathaniel had prepared for college under his uncle Rev. Israel Chauncy of Stratford — one of Yale's founders. After receiving his degree he taught at Hopkins Grammar School in Hadley and Springfield, then settled in Durham, Connecticut, as its first minister in 1706. He served Durham until his death 50 years later, in 1756. He was a Yale Fellow (1746-1752) and a published preacher — his election sermon of 1719 and his defense of regular singing (1728) circulated widely. In the theological disputes of his era he led the 'Old Light' faction. His sister Sarah married Rev. Samuel Whittlesey of Wallingford, connecting this branch to the Hooker family through the Newton line. (Yale Biographical Sketches)","body":"At Yale's inaugural commencement on September 13, 1702, Nathaniel Chauncey presented himself for a Bachelor's degree. The Corporation examined him and found him worthy of the higher degree — awarding him the M.A. instead. He was the only candidate at that first commencement to receive a degree by examination rather than transfer.","number":1},{"number":2,"category":"academia","header":"He came for a bachelor’s degree","body":"Presenting himself for a B.A. in 1702, Chauncey was advanced on the spot to Yale’s first Master of Arts — the college’s first degree awarded by examination. He preached at Durham for fifty years and sat as a Yale Fellow."}],"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Rev. Nathaniel Chauncey","first_name":"Nathaniel","last_name":"Chauncey","title":"Reverend","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"career":[{"role":"Minister","organization":"Durham, Connecticut","start_year":1706,"end_year":1756},{"role":"Fellow","organization":"Yale College","start_year":1746,"end_year":1752}],"slug":"nathaniel-chauncey-1681"}},"burialCemetery":null,"institutionsById":{"INST002":{"id":"INST002","primary_name":"Harvard College","name":"Harvard College","short_name":"Harvard","alt_names":[],"type":"university","founding_year":1636,"location":{"city":"Cambridge","state":"Massachusetts"},"primary_persons":[],"hooker_connected_people":["H00061","I00137","HD1175","X02364","H00028","HD2332","H00007","HD2978","HD0374","HD1641","I00004","HD0888","U00014","HD3350","H00071","I00112","I00002","I00111","HD0372","HD3129","I00005","I00003","H00008","X02366","HD2981","HD3150","HD1149","HD2443","HD0313","HD0309","H00219","T00036","HD3127","U00023","H00036","HD3177","HD0310","T00448","HD0102","HD3286","HD4421","HD0610","H00044","H01554","HD3790","T00063","HD04851","I00060","HD0308","HD2337","H00024","H00038","I00007","H00016","T00073","T00075","H01403","H01407","H00608","HD0886","HD1167","HD1234","HD1321","HD1585","HD1639","HD1759","H00914","HD1998","HD2051","HD2152","HD2154","HD2329","HD2334","HD2345","HD2362","HD2363","HD2413","HD2606","HD3080","HD3082","HD3099","HD3126","HD3131","H